HEADWORD: Xylitone
<hw>Xy"li*tone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A yellow oil having a geraniumlike odor, produced as a side product
in making phorone; -- called also <altname>xylite
oil</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

